'''Jordy José Alcívar Macías''' (born 5 August 1999) is an Ecuadorean professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] or [[defender (football)|defender]] for [[C.S.D. Independiente del Valle|Independiente del Valle]] and the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]].

==Club career==
Alcívar started his career with LDU Quito, where he was nicknamed "La Bochorna 44" after his video game username.<ref name="bendito">[https://www.benditofutbol.com/liga-de-quito/jordy-alcivar-mundialista-vive-complejo.html Jordy Alcívar, el mundialista que vive en el complejo de Liga de Quito] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210724001459/https://www.benditofutbol.com/liga-de-quito/jordy-alcivar-mundialista-vive-complejo.html |date=24 July 2021 }} benditofutbol.com</ref>

On 18 October 2021, it was announced that he would join newly-formed [[Major League Soccer]] side [[Charlotte FC]] in January 2022 on a four-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/charlotte-fc-sign-ecuador-youth-international-jordy-alcivar|title=Charlotte FC sign Ecuador youth international Jordy Alcivar|publisher=[[Major League Soccer]]|date=18 October 2021|accessdate=18 November 2021}}</ref>

He scored his first goal for Charlotte FC on 10 April 2022 against [[Atlanta United FC]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.charlottefootballclub.com/news/jordy-alcivar-i-m-only-going-to-get-better-with-every-match|title=Jordy Alcívar: "I'm only going to get better with every match" &#124; Charlotte FC|first=|last=|website=Charlotte Football Club}}</ref>

On 24 November 2022, Alcívar was transferred to [[Ecuadorian Serie A]] side [[C.S.D. Independiente del Valle|Independiente del Valle]].<ref>{{cite web |website=mlssoccer.com |publisher=Major League Soccer L.L.C. (MLS) |url=https://www.mlssoccer.com/news/charlotte-fc-transfer-jordy-alcivar-to-independiente-del-valle-of-ecuador |title=Charlotte FC transfer Jordy Alcívar to Ecuador's Independiente del Valle
|date=24 Nov 2022 |access-date=10 Sep 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
In 2019, he won the U-20 South American Championship,<ref>[https://www.eldiario.ec/noticias-manabi-ecuador/503916-jordy-el-seleccionado-sub-20-que-se-ha-convertido-orgullo-del-barrio-abdon-calderon-de-manta/ Jordy, el seleccionado sub 20 que se ha convertido orgullo del barrio Abdón Calderón de Manta] eldiario.ec</ref> and helped Ecuador come third at the U-20 World Cup in Poland.<ref name="bendito"/>

